{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Reporters at Bloomberg News were told to use the terminals to get an edge in the competitive world of financial journalism, more than half a dozen former employees said.", "abstract": "Former Bloomberg News employees say that reporters were trained to use function on company's financial data terminals that allowed them to view subscribers' contact information and, in some cases, monitor login activity in order to advance news coverage; more than 315,000 subscribers worldwide use terminals for instant market news, trading information and communication; company has acknowledged reporters' access after Goldman Sachs complained.", "section_name": "Business Day", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Amy", "role": "reported", "lastname": "CHOZICK", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By AMY CHOZICK", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2013/05/13/business/media/bloomberg-admits-terminal-snooping.html", "lead_paragraph": "Reporters at Bloomberg News were told to use the terminals to get an edge in the competitive world of financial journalism, more than half a dozen former employees said.", "headline": {"main": "Bloomberg Admits Terminal Snooping", "print_headline": "Bloomberg Admits Terminal Snooping"}, "_id": "5190d98840e9ec457e2a0d23", "word_count": "1028", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2013/05/13/business/sub-jp-bloomberg/sub-jp-bloomberg-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2013/05/13/business/sub-jp-bloomberg/sub-jp-bloomberg-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2013/05/13/business/sub-jp-bloomberg/sub-jp-bloomberg-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2013/05/13/business/sub-jp-bloomberg/sub-jp-bloomberg-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"},